article.headline: Central Michigan 90, Evansville 73
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Kevin Nelson scored a career-high 27 points to lead Central Michigan past Evansville 90-73 on Saturday. The Chippewas (5-20) built a 52-29 halftime lead as they shot 56 percent in the first half and the Purple Aces (5-19) went the final 7:23 of the period without hitting a field goal. In the second half, the Chippewas shot just 23 percent but hit 23 of 29 free throws. Evansville cut Central's lead to just 12 points with 10:54 left in the game, but Nelson sank a pair of three-pointers and Dan Quinn added a lay-up to give the Chippewas a 20-point lead. Gerrit Brigitha finished with 20 points for Central Michigan, while T.J. Meerman scored 11 points off the bench. Clint Cuffle led Evansville with 11 points and 10 rebounds, while Bradley Strickland and Eric Ottens each added 10 points. The game featured 59 personal fouls and took over two and a half hours to play.
